- Preferences: pristinely remastered rock/pop that preserves transient snap, analogue warmth and micro‑dynamics via restrained mastering; clear headroom; tactile keys and punchy, well‑defined bass and drums; presence‑forward, close‑miked, dry and intelligible lead vocals; tight doubling/controlled compression; layered harmonies that thicken choruses without burying the lead; piano‑ or guitar‑forward arrangements; warm tape sheen; live‑in‑studio immediacy; wide stereo imaging; preserved full‑length solos; polished mixes with good instrument separation and front‑to‑back depth.
